&lt;p&gt;&lt;img data-src=&#34;https://gitee.com/rogeeerluo/PicGoPics/raw/master/image-20210825173720263.png&#34; alt=&#34;image-20210825173720263&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
$$
\dot A_{vL}= \frac{j\omega R_2 C_2}{1+j\omega R_2C_2}=\frac{1}{1-j(f_L/f)}\ \ when \ f_L=\frac{1}{2\pi R_1C_1}
\\ |\dot A _{vM}|=\frac 1{\sqrt{1+(f_L/f)^2}},\ \varphi =arctan(f_L/f)
$$
